Joso is seventeen years old and lives in Helsinki, the capital of Finland. She wants to go to college to become a nurse. In November 2015, she became pregnant and decided that she wanted to have an abortion. She made a choice four men never could. And amazing that the decision on whether she can have an abortion or not was made by the same four men. Joso didn’t expect the process to be so complicated and involved in bureaucracy. One of the problems she encountered at the hospital was telling her parents. Joso doesn’t have a good relationship with her parents, and she feared that they would not agree with her choice. She was right about their feelings – they didn’t approve of her decision and even tried to persuade her not to terminate the pregnancy.
